'''Dire-Dawa University''' is a public university located in  [[Dire-Dawa]], [[Ethiopia]]. It opened for the 2006&ndash;07 academic year with 754 students, as one of 13 new universities started by the Ministry of Higher Education, Federal Democratic Republic of Ethiopia.<ref>[http://www.ddu.edu.et/public/news/?p=32#more-32 Welcome to Dire-Dawa University], Dire Dawa University, June 15, 2011.</ref><ref>[http://allafrica.com/stories/200703120374.html "Ethiopia: University Welcomes First Batch for more info contact the official website,"], ''[[The Ethiopian Herald]]'', 12 March 2007, at AllAfrica.com.</ref>

